author: @berglerlemur
text: Hi Corey, your videos are definitely some of the best Python tutorials out there. But one thing I feel is missing is accompanying excercises. It would be great if in the video descriptions for each video there were some practice problems to solve. I feel like it's a huge part of learning.   I know that there are excercises available online and in books but it would be great if there were CSchafer ones that married up perfectly with the video content.  Even if you suggested that viewers posted excercises in the comments, a great way for the experienced to teach/challenge the inexperienced.
